  "title": "CONSTRUCTION TECHNICIAN",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Duties & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Estimating project costs ahead of bidding for new contracts</li><li>Negotiating with suppliers on the cost of materials, equipment and labour</li><li>Checking the quality of suppliers</li><li>Helping to plan each construction stage</li><li>Drafting plans and blueprints using CAD (computer aided design) software</li><li>Monitoring build progress</li><li>Preparing sites before construction work begins</li><li>Supervising contractor teams</li><li>Working on a construction site or in an office.</li></ul><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>*Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent.</p><p>*Familiarity with design software (eg. Autodesk, AutoCad Civil 3D, and MicroStation)</p><p>*Knowledge of map creation software and photo imaging software</p><p>*Strong Analytical and critical thinking skills with high level of accuracy in calculations and design</p><p>*Good interpersonal skills, positive attitude and pro-active</p><p>*Willing to work day and night</p><p>*To comply with the policies and procedures of the company.</p><p>*Long term commitment</p><p>*Possesses local Class 3 and/or Class 4 driving license an added advantage</p><p><br />\n\n</p>",
